      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIG MAN ZOR (3) landed midfield in a slowly run 2200m event last start but closed well when beaten 2.1L at Northam last time out. He'll need a touch of luck from the draw, but he'll be better for the run at this trip last start. Last start rating stacks up and if he can raise the bar again, he'll be hard to beat. LUKA MAGIC (8) missed by 0.8L in a solid performance when out to 1700m for the first time a fortnight ago. Out in trip again now looks ideal and he continues to improve. He was a 30-1 pop there, but the last start figure is strong and with further improvement expected, he can get the job done. YALDA NIGHT (1) just missed last start, coming through the same race as BIG MAN ZOR. He's been a maiden for a while now, but this sets up favourably and Nottle remains in the saddle. He can land the knockout blow. SIN CITY BOY (6) can improve getting right out in distance. HE'SNOTALLTHERE (7) won't be far away stepping out to 2200m for the first time.",
